Vale SA (VALE3) , the worldâ€™s largest iron-ore
producer, will invest $3 billion for a coal-to-liquids plant to
be set up near its Moatize mine, Televisao
de Mocambique reported today, citing Chief Executive Officer
 Roger Agnelli .  The plant would produce 300 million liters of fuel per year
